/******************************************************************************
 * PRODUCT CONTROLLER
 ******************************************************************************

/*
 * =============================================================================
 * INTRODUCTION
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * ProductController is the entry point of the Product API.
 *
 * It receives HTTP requests from the frontend
 * and delegates the business logic to the service layer.
 *
 * The controller should NOT contain business logic.
 * Its responsibility is only to:
 *
 * • Receive requests
 * • Validate input (if required)
 * • Call the service layer
 * • Return the response
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * WHY DO WE NEED A CONTROLLER?
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * The frontend cannot directly communicate with the database.
 *
 * Instead,
 *
 * React
 *    │
 *    ▼
 * ProductController
 *    │
 *    ▼
 * ProductService
 *    │
 *    ▼
 * Repository
 *    │
 *    ▼
 * Database
 *
 * Controller acts as a bridge between client and backend.
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * ANNOTATIONS USED
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * @RestController
 * ----------------
 * Marks this class as a REST API.
 *
 * @RequestMapping("/api/v1/products")
 * -----------------------------------
 * Base URL for all product endpoints.
 *
 * @CrossOrigin(...)
 * ----------------
 * Allows React application running on another port
 * to access this API.
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * COMPLETE EXECUTION FLOW
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * React Application
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * Axios GET Request
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * ProductController
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * ProductService
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * ProductRepository
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * MySQL Database
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * Product List
 *       │
 *       ▼
 * JSON Response
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * CONCLUSION
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * Controller handles incoming HTTP requests and delegates
 * all business operations to the service layer.
 */
