/*
 * =============================================================================
 * INTRODUCTION
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * Service layer contains business logic.
 *
 * Controllers should not directly communicate with repositories.
 *
 * Instead,
 *
 * Controller
 *      │
 *      ▼
 * Service
 *      │
 *      ▼
 * Repository
 *
 * This separation follows Spring Boot layered architecture.
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * WHY SERVICE LAYER?
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * • Keeps Controller clean.
 * • Business rules remain centralized.
 * • Easy to test.
 * • Easy to maintain.
 * • Multiple controllers can reuse the same service.
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * ANNOTATION
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * @Service
 *
 * Registers this class as a Spring Service Bean.
 *
 * Spring automatically creates its object.
 *
 * =============================================================================
 * CONCLUSION
 * =============================================================================
 *
 * Service layer acts as the brain of the application.
 */
